U.S. President Joe Biden recently signed an executive order to dispose of the assets of the Central Bank of Afghanistan in the United States. The Afghan central bank's $7 billion in U.S. assets will be divided equally, half as compensation funds for victims of the September 11 attacks and for the distribution of funds to humanitarian organizations providing assistance. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Aaron Liu argues that the U.S. is like a robber.